## ğŸ“¦ Installation

### 1. Download the Plugin
Download the latest version of the ShipFlo plugin from our GitHub repository:  
â¡ï¸ [https://github.com/shipflo-inc/shipflo-wc](https://github.com/shipflo-inc/shipflo-wc)

### 2. Upload & Install via WordPress Admin
1. Log in to your **WordPress Admin Panel**.  
2. Navigate to **Plugins â†’ Add New**.  
3. Click **Upload Plugin** at the top.  
4. Choose the `shipflo-wc.zip` file you downloaded.  
5. Click **Install Now**, then **Activate Plugin**.

Your ShipFlo plugin is now installed and active.

---

## ğŸ”‘ Connect WooCommerce with ShipFlo

### Step 1: Generate API Key in ShipFlo
1. Log in to your **[ShipFlo Dashboard](https://app.shipflo.com)**.  
2. Go to your **Profile** â†’ click the **three-dot menu (â‹®)**.  
3. Select **Generate API Key** and click **Run**.  
4. Copy the generated **API key** and close the dialog box.

### Step 2: Configure in WooCommerce
1. Log in to your **WordPress Admin Panel**.  
2. Go to **WooCommerce â†’ Settings â†’ ShipFlo** tab.  
3. Paste the **API Key** you copied from ShipFlo.  
4. Click **Save Changes**.

âœ… Your WooCommerce store is now connected to ShipFlo.

